
################################################################################

read-ipod: This application is used to read the ipod version from ipod chip:-
In the examples below 0x10 is the ipod chip i2c address and 0x00 is the sub-addr

	To read-ipod Device Version:-
	Ford:
		./read-ipod 0x10 0x00
			Read 0x00 = 0x03 (ipod-2.0b)
	Toyota:
		./read-ipod 0x10 0x00
			Read 0x00 = 0x05 (ipod-2.0c)
	Orinoco:
		./read-ipod 0x10 0x00
			Read 0x00 = 0x03 (ipod-2.0b)

To compile the appication:-
	$(CROSS_COMPILE)-gcc -o read-ipod read_ipod.c
		OR
	$(CROSS_COMPILE)-gcc --static -o read-ipod read_ipod.c

################################################################################

camera-test: This application is used to test camera preview and stability.

Precondition: Camera connected, and launch the application
	1. show preview without scrolling
	2. show jbl logo when camera signal is lost
	3. show camera preview when signal recovers

Precondition: Camera not connected and app is launched
	1. show blue screen

To compile: $(CROSS_COMPILE)-gcc cam-test.c -o cam-test -lg2d -lpthread

To test:
	./cam-test

################################################################################

partitioning-script:- This script is used to generate partition tables
based on a config file. The config file can be modified to get any layout.

	Usage:
		./generate-flash-script.sh  -c config/ford-v2.conf
